gomodel:SYNGO_4164  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors isolate highly purified clathrin-coated vesicles (CCVs) from mouse brain. In the results section they state \"Detailed analysis of CCV samples by mass spectrometry revealed that the large majority of CCVs seems to be derived from the synapses, yet some CCV come from neuronal cell body/intracellular membranes...\" A mass spectrometry analysis of these CCVs reveals auxilin (DNAJC6). Given extensive evidence of a BP for auxilin in synaptic vesicle recycling, it is highly likely that this identification represents auxilin on pre-synpatic CCVs.. Experimental description: First line of results, \"We have prepared CCVs from mouse brain....\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4164" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

